<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8"/>
<title>MKTG 4333 · Chapter 11 · Distribution deck</title>
<style>
  :root{
    --bg:#f5f2ec; --ink:#1a1a1a; --ink-soft:#4A4A4A; --ink-mute:#7A7A7A;
    --rule:#E8E6E1; --accent:#DA7756; --accent-tint:#FDF6F3;
    --font:'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
  }
  *{ margin:0; padding:0; box-sizing:border-box; }
  html,body{ background:var(--bg); font-family:var(--font); color:var(--ink); }
  body{ padding:64px 72px 96px; }
  header{
    display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:flex-end;
    border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule); padding-bottom:20px; margin-bottom:36px;
  }
  header .dot{ display:inline-block; width:10px; height:10px; background:var(--accent); border-radius:50%; margin-right:10px; vertical-align:middle; }
  header h1{ font-size:32px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:-0.01em; }
  header h1 em{ font-style:italic; color:var(--accent); font-weight:500; }
  header .meta{
    font-size:11px; letter-spacing:0.12em; text-transform:uppercase;
    color:var(--ink-mute); font-weight:600;
  }
  .intro{
    max-width:70ch; font-size:18px; line-height:1.55; color:var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom:44px;
  }
  .intro a{ color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; border-bottom:1px solid var(--accent); }
  .grid{
    display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(420px, 1fr));
    gap:28px;
  }
  .card{
    background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--rule);
    display:flex; flex-direction:column; overflow:hidden;
    transition: transform .2s, box-shadow .2s;
  }
  .card:hover{ transform:translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 8px 24px -10px rgba(0,0,0,.15); }
  .card .frame{
    position:relative; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9; overflow:hidden; background:#ffffff;
    border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .card .frame .scaler{
    position:absolute; top:0; left:0;
    width:960px; height:540px;
    transform-origin: top left;
  }
  .card .frame iframe{
    width:960px; height:540px; border:0; display:block; pointer-events:none;
    background:#ffffff;
  }
  .card .info{ padding:16px 22px; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:baseline; gap:12px; }
  .card .info h3{ font-size:16px; font-weight:600; line-height:1.3; }
  .card .info .n{
    font-size:11px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:0.14em; color:var(--ink-mute);
    text-transform:uppercase; white-space:nowrap;
  }
  .card .info .tmpl{ display:block; font-size:12px; color:var(--ink-soft); margin-top:3px; font-style:italic; }
  .card a.open{
    display:block; text-align:right; font-size:11px; letter-spacing:0.12em;
    text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--accent); font-weight:600;
    padding:0 22px 16px; text-decoration:none;
  }
  footer{
    margin-top:64px; padding-top:20px; border-top:1px solid var(--rule);
    font-size:13px; color:var(--ink-mute); display:flex; justify-content:space-between;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1><span class="dot"></span>Chapter 11 · <em>Distribution</em>.</h1>
    <span class="meta">MKTG 4333 · 20 slides · 960 × 540</span>
  </header>

  <p class="intro">
    A teaching deck on distribution and marketing channels, built on the coral design system. One claim per slide,
    white backgrounds, one coral element per slide, Segoe UI throughout. It runs the chapter's arc: a buyer who
    cannot find you cannot buy you, the four utilities a channel produces, channel length from zero to three tiers,
    the markup-versus-margin arithmetic and the price waterfall, the intensity ladder, push and pull, the five
    French-Raven powers, the DTC unit-economics math, the conflict-response taxonomy, and the three brand systems
    (Costco, Trader Joe's, Stanley). Read the system rules in
    <a href="../DESIGN-SYSTEM.md">DESIGN-SYSTEM.md</a> and
    <a href="../CHART-PRINCIPLES.md">CHART-PRINCIPLES.md</a>.
  </p>

  <div class="grid" id="grid"></div>

<script>
(() => {
  const slides = [
    ["01-title.html",             "01", "Distribution, where a buyer who cannot find you cannot buy you", "Title / cover"],
    ["02-divider-availability.html","02","A correctly priced offer is half the job", "Section divider"],
    ["03-walmart-germany.html",   "03", "Walmart's price was right; the channel was wrong for Germany", "Two-column"],
    ["04-four-utilities.html",    "04", "A working channel closes four gaps between making and using", "Exhibit · four utilities"],
    ["05-divider-design.html",    "05", "Channel design is one reach-for-control trade-off", "Section divider"],
    ["06-channel-length.html",    "06", "Channel length runs zero to three tiers", "Exhibit · chapter fig-1"],
    ["07-markup-margin.html",     "07", "A 100% markup is only a 50% margin on the same unit", "Two-column"],
    ["08-price-waterfall.html",   "08", "Through two tiers the maker keeps $0.36; direct, $1.92", "Exhibit · chapter price waterfall"],
    ["09-divider-intensity.html", "09", "Every commercial pressure pushes a brand toward intensive", "Section divider"],
    ["10-intensity-ladder.html",  "10", "Exclusive, selective, intensive; the rung is a decision you defend", "Exhibit · chapter fig-2"],
    ["11-push-pull.html",         "11", "Push spends on the channel, pull spends on the buyer", "Two-column"],
    ["12-five-powers.html",       "12", "Expert and referent produce the largest empirical lift", "Exhibit · chapter five-powers map"],
    ["13-caterpillar.html",       "13", "Komatsu was 40% cheaper and still could not take the share", "Two-column"],
    ["14-divider-omni.html",      "14", "Omni-channel is the 2026 default", "Section divider"],
    ["15-dtc-cohort.html",        "15", "A wholesale buffer absorbs the acquisition-cost shock", "Comparison bars"],
    ["16-conflict-response.html", "16", "A partner sliding from voice to neglect warns you first", "Exhibit · conflict response"],
    ["17-divider-system.html",    "17", "Read the channel as one interlocking system", "Section divider"],
    ["18-trader-joes.html",       "18", "Trader Joe's earns $2,000 per square foot against $600", "Comparison bars"],
    ["19-three-brands.html",      "19", "Each layer does one job no other layer can", "KPI row"],
    ["20-closing.html",           "20", "Run the one-page channel audit on a brand you shop", "Closing / takeaways"]
  ];
  const grid = document.getElementById('grid');
  slides.forEach(([href, n, claim, tmpl]) => {
    const card = document.createElement('article');
    card.className = 'card';
    card.innerHTML =
      '<div class="frame"><div class="scaler"><iframe src="' + href + '?thumb=1" title="' + claim + '"></iframe></div></div>' +
      '<div class="info"><div><h3>' + claim + '</h3><span class="tmpl">' + tmpl + '</span></div><span class="n">' + n + '</span></div>' +
      '<a class="open" href="' + href + '" target="_blank">Open &rarr;</a>';
    grid.appendChild(card);
  });

  function fitCards(){
    document.querySelectorAll('.card .frame').forEach(frame => {
      const scaler = frame.querySelector('.scaler');
      if (!scaler) return;
      const w = frame.clientWidth;
      const s = w / 960;
      scaler.style.transform = 'scale(' + s + ')';
      scaler.style.width  = '960px';
      scaler.style.height = '540px';
      frame.style.height = (540 * s) + 'px';
    });
  }
  document.querySelectorAll('iframe').forEach(f => {
    f.addEventListener('load', () => {
      try { f.contentDocument.documentElement.classList.add('is-thumb'); } catch(_){}
    });
  });
  window.addEventListener('resize', fitCards);
  window.addEventListener('load', fitCards);
  fitCards();
})();
</script>

  <footer>
    <span>MKTG 4333 · Prof. Felipe M. Affonso · Spears School of Business</span>
    <span>White bg · Segoe UI · one coral accent · pairs with the Ch 11 chapter</span>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
